  "body": "In node e2e, we have the `stop-services` option to keep the services running after test for further debug. \n\nHowever, we set `Pdeathsig` to `SIGTERM` for the services, which means that once the parent exits, they will receive `SIGTERM` and exit with the parent if they don't trap the signal.\nWith this, `stop-services` option will never work.\n\nIf we still need this feature, we should not set `Pdeathsig` if `stop-services` is false.\n\n@vishh \n/cc @kubernetes/sig-node \n",
